{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionMedical image segmentation is a significant study area in computer vision, to classify medical pictures at the pixel level and then precisely segment the target item.",
    "Segmentation datasets are created from unimodal or multimodal pictures obtained by professional medical equipment such as magnetic resonance imaging (MRI), computed tomography (CT), and ultrasonography (US).",
    "Traditional nondeep learning medical picture segmentation approaches depend mostly on thresholding [1], region growth [2], border detection [3], and other techniques.",
    "To produce superior segmentation results, picture features must be manually extracted before segmentation.",
    "The feature extraction methods for various datasets are frequently diverse, and some professional experience is necessary [4][5][6]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Traditional nondeep learning medical picture segmentation approaches depend mostly on thresholding [1], region growth [2], border detection [3], and other techniques.",
    "The feature extraction methods for various datasets are frequently diverse, and some professional experience is necessary [4][5][6]."
